<Author>toomuchtravel
<Content>At Home at the Homewood Stayed here one night while attending a conference at the Hyatt Hotel, which is across from the Convention Center. From the moment I walked in, I felt like I was at home. The staff was very friendly and accomodating with special requests. The suite was a little larger that typical and was very clean with everything in good working order. Wireless worked perfectly. Bathroom was plenty big enough and clean.The evening reception included hamburgers with all the fixings that night and were tasty, along with beer, wine, soda, etc. There was no need to leave for an expensive dinner. It is a few minutes walk to the convention center and the downtown free transit zone. With the free transit zone, you can get on a bus and go just about anywhere downtown - makes the hills not as much of a challenge! I would stay here again in a heartbeat, especially if had my family with me. 
