<Author>none_7
<Content>Would not recommend We stayed at this hotel in downtown Seattle on Pike St. in July 2008. It had recently become a Homewood Suites and you could tell that the lobby area had been newly renovated. It just goes to show you though, don't judge a book by its cover. I stay at many Hilton properties for business travel and this hotel was not up to standard. The staff was Seattle hip but not particularly helpful and friendly. They didn't really get the concept of making sure the customer was happy. I was told one thing over the phone before I arrived regarding roll away beds, and given a completely different answer when I got there. I made a special request to accommodate allergies that other hotels can manage, and they couldn't do without a lot of phone calls and proding. Our room was small and cramped. It would be fine for one person, but not for three. We were not comfortable there. In fact, we had booked additional days which I promptly canceled and we moved to another location. Lots of the rooms face the freeway, so be aware of the noise factor if you do book there. We would definitely not stay there again. 
